---
title: QR Verification Flow (target < 200ms p99)
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor Consumer as Consumer (Mobile)
    participant API as NestJS API\n/verify/:uuid
    participant Redis as Redis Cache\n(TTL: 5min)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL\ncertification schema

    Consumer->>API: GET /verify/{uuid}?sig={hmac}
    Note over API: No authentication required (public endpoint)

    API->>Redis: GET qr:{uuid}
    alt Cache HIT (~10-50ms)
        Redis-->>API: Cached certification data
        API-->>Consumer: 200 OK { valid: true, certificationNumber, ... }
    else Cache MISS
        Redis-->>API: null

        Note over API: Validate HMAC-SHA256 signature
        Note over API: crypto.timingSafeEqual(expected, received)

        alt Invalid signature
            API-->>Consumer: 403 Forbidden { valid: false, error: "INVALID_SIGNATURE" }
        else Valid signature
            API->>DB: SELECT certification WHERE qr_code.uuid = ?
            DB-->>API: Certification + product + cooperative data

            alt QR not found
                API-->>Consumer: 404 Not Found
            else QR found (status = granted)
                API->>Redis: SET qr:{uuid} data EX 300
                API-->>Consumer: 200 OK { valid: true, certificationNumber, productName, cooperativeName, grantedAt }
            else QR found (status = revoked)
                API-->>Consumer: 200 OK { valid: false, revoked: true }
            end
        end
    end
